istico Statale "M. M. Lazzaro" di Catania</desc></graphic></surface><surface type="front"><graphic n="screen" width="4272px" height = "2856px" url="Ursino218-front.jpg"><desc>Photograph by Liceo Artistico Statale "M. M. Lazzaro" di Catania</desc></graphic></surface><surface type="scale"><graphic n="screen" width="5520px" height = "3680px" url="Ursino218-scale.jpg"><desc>Photograph by Liceo Artistico Statale "M. M. Lazzaro" di Catania</desc></graphic></surface><surface type="?"><graphic n="screen" width="5616px" height = "3744px" url="Ursino218-scale_b.jpg"><desc>Photograph by Liceo Artistico Statale "M. M. Lazzaro" di Catania</desc></graphic></surface><surface type="threequarter"><graphic n="screen" width="4752px" height = "3168px" url="Ursino218-threequarter.jpg"><desc>Photograph by Liceo Artistico Statale "M. M. Lazzaro" di Catania</desc></graphic></surface></facsimile><text><body><div type="edition" xml:lang="la"><ab> <lb n="1"/><persName><name>Martur<lb n="2" break="no"/>a</name></persName> in pace <g type="orans">((orans))</g> <g type="avis in mensa">((avis in mensa))</g></ab></div><div type="apparatus"><p></p></div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP"><p>Martyra, in peace</p></div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#SA"><p>Martira, in pace </p></div><div type="commentary" xml:lang="en"><p>Martyra is a common Christian name (from the Greek, meaning ‘witness’). The praying figure and the bird are both common in Christian funerary imagery, although the interpretation of the object beneath the bird is uncertain.</p></div><div type="commentary" xml:lang="it"><p resp="#SA">NA</p><p>Martyra è un nome cristiano comune (dal greco, che significa "testimone"). La figura orante e l'uccello sono entrambi comuni nelle immagini funerarie cristiane, anche se l'interpretazione dell'oggetto sotto l'uccello è incerta.</p></div><div type="bibliography"><listBibl><bibl type="IMusCatania"><citedRange>352</citedRange><ptr target="http://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/2EUC82DH"/></bibl><bibl><ref target="#MA1960"/><citedRange unit="page">83</citedRange></bibl><bibl><ref target="#PS2006"/><citedRange unit="page">118</citedRange></bibl><bibl><ref target="#Ko2004"/><citedRange unit="number">352</citedRange></bibl></listBibl></div></body></text></TEI>